    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>French and English staff weapons used between the 12th and 14th centuries, having a pointed head with a scythelike blade and a fluke on the back.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
